@@ -114,12 +114,17 @@ Before uploading, the sidebar calls **`GET /api/extension/workflows/:id`**; if t
 
 Sidebars use `extension/sidebars-api.js`:
 
-- `GET /api/extension/sidebars` – List connected sidebars
-- `POST /api/extension/sidebars/register` – Register/upsert sidebar
-- `PATCH /api/extension/sidebars/:id` – Update sidebar name or project
-- `POST /api/extension/sidebars/disconnect` – Disconnect
+- `GET` / `HEAD` `/api/extension/sidebars` – List connected sidebars (`HEAD`: same auth/query/DB filter, empty body). Response includes `connected` from `last_seen` (~1h threshold) unless `omit_connected=1`/`true`/`yes`. Optional query: `since` (ISO 8601); `limit` (integer 1–200). Response `Cache-Control: private, no-store`, `Vary: Authorization`.
+- `POST /api/extension/sidebars/register` – Register/upsert sidebar (`window_id` max 512 chars, `sidebar_name` max 256). Optional `active_project_id` must be a project **you** own (**404** if the UUID is not yours).
+- `GET` / `PATCH` / `POST` `/api/extension/sidebars/:id` – `:id` must be a UUID. Update sidebar name or project; non-null `active_project_id` must be your project (**404**). Empty body refreshes `last_seen` (heartbeat). **`POST`** aliases `PATCH` if a relay only allows POST.
+- `POST /api/extension/sidebars/heartbeat` – Refresh `last_seen` only: send **exactly one** of `sidebar_id` (UUID) or `window_id` (**400** if both); or MCP batch `{ backend_ids: string[] }` only (Supabase UUIDs, max 64, deduped). Batch response: `{ updated, requested, skipped, sidebars }` (`skipped` = unknown / not-owned ids).
+- `POST /api/extension/sidebars/disconnect` – Disconnect; **exactly one** of `sidebar_id` (UUID) or `window_id` (**400** if both).
 
-**`window_id`:** The extension registers with `${ChromeWindowId}_sidepanel` (stable for that browser window, independent of the active tab). The API should upsert on `(user_id, window_id)` and refresh `last_seen_at` on each register. Purge or hide rows that are stale long-term; legacy rows may use older `windowId_tabId` shapes.
+**Local MCP** (`mcp-server`, `GET /api/sidebars`): With query `since`, `limit`, and/or `omit_connected`, proxies to `GET /api/extension/sidebars` on the host through the extension relay (same auth as other sidebar relay calls). If the relay is down or the proxy fails, returns the in-memory list for this machine only.
+
+**MCP relay** (`mcp/mcp-relay.html`): `BACKEND_FETCH` uses **`ExtensionConfig.APP_ORIGIN`** (from `extension/config.js`, loaded before `mcp-relay.js`). Optional override: `chrome.storage.local.cfsBackendApiOrigin` (string, no trailing slash). Defaults to `https://www.extensiblecontent.com` if config is missing.
+
+**`window_id`:** The side panel registers with `${deviceId}_sidepanel` (stable device id from storage). The API upserts on `(user_id, window_id)` and refreshes `last_seen` on register and heartbeat. Legacy rows may use older `windowId_tabId` or numeric `_sidepanel` shapes.
 
